      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation against in-vitro blood damage measurements",
      "description": "Predicted normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in-vitro measurements from five operating conditions. Computed RH values range 0.71–0.94 against predicate, satisfying the RH < 1 acceptance criterion at all points. Inherent biological variability in red blood cell fragility across donor samples was assessed qualitatively by subject-matter experts and noted in the technical report narrative; structured probabilistic characterization of this aleatory source was deferred pending additional donor-sample data. Model predictions fall within the qualitatively described band of expected variability."
